Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (peeling optional).

Pop the wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the potatoes have 5 mins left to cook, place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the pan is very hot, sear the @Irish beef strips{250%grams} until cooked through, shifting as it colours, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Remove the pan from the heat.

Stir through the @Ballymaloe tomato relish{1%pot} with a knob of @butter{to taste}. Toss to coat and season to taste with salt and pepper.

Chop the @tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

Toss the @salad leaves{40%grams} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, the @balsamic glaze{2%sachets} and the tomato.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the potato wedges, flavourful beef strips and salad between plates.

Crumble the @Greek style cheese{100%grams} over the salad.